==English==

===Interjection===
'''meh'''

# An interjection expressing [[indifference]], [[apathy]], or "[[I don't know]]"; the verbal equivalent of a shrug of the shoulders
#: ''"What do you want for dinner?" &mdash; "Meh.  I'm not really hungry."''
#: ''"Where is the stapler?" &mdash; "Meh.  I haven't seen it in days."

* Widely used due to popular show "The Simpsons".
----
#Actually, "meh" was first thought of by Jeff Huting, Adam Shirely, Marc Johnson and others in Waterloo, Iowa, over a decade ago. The group of friends was trying to find the word that could be said with the absolute least amount of effort. By barely opening the mouth and just barely using the vocal cords enough to make a sound, a word best described as "meh" came from their mouths.

"meh" stands for being too lazy to care to give a definitive answer.

For example, if someone asks "Do you want to go to rent a movie?" and the person being asked feels as though it would require more effort then it would be worth, the person would reply "meh"

TO CORRECT THE DICTIONARY: "Meh" is used as a one word sentence. Saying "meh", and then following it with additional words or sentences defeats the purpose of the word altogether. THis is because, as said earlier, "meh" is the word that is used when one is feeling too lazy to say anything but bare minimum reply.

TO ADD TO THE DICTIONARY: "Hem" is the opposite of "Meh". If one expresses interest and would like to partake in a particular activity or suggestion, one replies "Hem" It is the inverted spelling of meh and therefore has an inverted meaning.

